Anonymous Sun 13 Sep 2020 11:14:20 No.32756954 Report
Quoted By:
>>32756518
There's two questions there, even if you didn't intend it.

A chapter, at least in the traditional novel sense, should be a coherent scene or scenes that represent a viewpoint with a reasonable beginning and end.
Plenty of writers break this. I've seen chapters as short as a few words. Brandon Sanderson wrote The Last Battle in the last book of TWoT as a massive chunk that continually switched POV characters.

As we're not doing that and as someone with a 150k+ word story, I'd say do not equate one scene with one chapter unless you accept having the occasional super-short update.
Shoot for 2k to 10k. Mine average to ~6K on that one, though the shortest is just over 1k and the longest over 15k.
